  "text": "Three core files handle memory-pressure eviction: (1) `api/types.go` defines the eviction signal `SignalMemoryAvailable = \"memory.available\"`, the `Threshold` struct, and the `OpForSignal` map that associates memory signals with the LessThan operator \u2014 these constitute the memory pressure eviction thresholds. (2) `eviction_manager.go` implements the eviction manager's decision logic in `synchronize()`, which checks thresholds against observations, ranks pods, and calls `evictPod()` to kill the chosen pod. (3) `helpers.go` maps `SignalMemoryAvailable` to the `NodeMemoryPressure` node condition (line 78) and to `v1.ResourceMemory` (line 90), and provides the `rankMemoryPressure` ranking function (line 1146) used by `buildSignalToRankFunc` to order pods for eviction under memory pressure.",
